# Archers vs Knights: Simulation Spec

## Overview

A grid-based auto-battler on a bounded rectangular map. Red archers (ranged) fight blue knights (melee) until one faction is eliminated. Units spawn randomly, then act deterministically ‚ÄĒ no randomness after the initial placement.

The simulation is turn-based. Each turn, every unit moves once and attacks once. Population decreases through combat until one side is gone.

---

## The Board

The board is a bounded rectangular grid. Default size: 320 x 144 cells. Coordinates range from (0, 0) to (map_width, map_height) inclusive.

There is no wrapping. The edges are impassable ‚ÄĒ boundary cells are treated as occupied. Units cannot move beyond or through them.

Each cell holds at most one unit. Units occupy exactly one cell.

---

## Unit Types

There are two unit types, differentiated by faction, stats, and movement behavior.

### Archer (Red Faction)

| Stat | Value |
|------|-------|
| Health | 10 |
| Attack Damage | 5 |
| Weapon Range | 3 (manhattan) |
| Movement Speed | 1 |
| Movement Type | kite |

Archers are fragile ranged units. They try to maintain distance from enemies, fleeing when knights get too close and approaching when they're out of range. They win by staying at range and shooting.

### Knight (Blue Faction)

| Stat | Value |
|------|-------|
| Health | 35 |
| Attack Damage | 5 |
| Weapon Range | 1 (manhattan) |
| Movement Speed | 1 |
| Movement Type | charge |

Knights are durable melee units. They close distance as fast as possible to engage in melee. They win by reaching archers and sustaining through their fire.

---

## Spawning

All units spawn on turn 1. The app_start system runs once, creates all units with random positions, then disables itself permanently.

**Default army sizes:** 1127 archers, 2649 knights (configurable in app.yaml).

**Placement:** For each unit, a random unoccupied cell is selected:
```
do { x = rand() % (map_width + 1); y = rand() % (map_height + 1); } while (occupied(x, y));
```

Knights spawn first, then archers. RNG is seeded once with `time(NULL) + offset`. This is the only source of randomness in the entire simulation. All behavior after spawning is deterministic.

---

## Turn Structure

Each turn executes these systems in order:

1. **despawn** ‚ÄĒ remove units with health <= 0 from previous turn
2. **start_of_turn** ‚ÄĒ clear TookDamage markers and Weapon.attacked fields
3. **app_start** ‚ÄĒ spawn armies (turn 1 only, then disabled)
4. **movement** ‚ÄĒ move each unit one step
5. **attack** ‚ÄĒ each unit attacks one enemy in range, records target in Weapon.attacked
6. **spawn** ‚ÄĒ process any SpawnRequest entities
7. **app_stop** ‚ÄĒ check win/loss conditions

A unit may both move and attack in the same turn. These are separate phases, not a choice.

---

## Movement

Every unit moves exactly one cell per turn (speed is always 1). Movement is resolved iteratively until no unit can improve its position.

### Distance Fields

Before movement begins, two BFS distance fields are computed:
- Distance from every cell to the nearest red (archer) unit
- Distance from every cell to the nearest blue (knight) unit

These are multi-source BFS flood fills ‚ÄĒ O(cells), not O(units squared). Each unit uses the appropriate enemy distance field to score candidate moves.

### Candidate Moves

Each unit evaluates 5 candidates: the 4 adjacent cells plus staying in place. Occupied cells (except current position) and out-of-bounds cells are excluded.

### Scoring

**Knights (charge):**
```
score = -distance_to_nearest_enemy
```
Minimize distance to the closest archer. Move toward enemies.

**Archers (kite):**
```
if distance_to_nearest_enemy >= attack_range:
    if enemies_in_range > 0:
        score = 20000 + enemies_in_range    # hold and shoot
    else:
        score = -distance_to_nearest_enemy  # approach to range
else:
    score = distance_to_nearest_enemy * 1000  # flee
```
If safe (enemy outside melee range), prefer cells with targets in attack range. If unsafe (enemy within melee range), flee with high priority.

### Tiebreaking

When multiple cells share the best score:

1. **Knights only ‚ÄĒ ally backing:** prefer cells where an allied unit is directly behind (at the reflection point of the move direction). This encourages formation.
2. **All units ‚ÄĒ centrality:** prefer cells closest to the map center (manhattan distance to (map_width/2, map_height/2)).
3. **Fallback:** first candidate in iteration order.

### Iteration

Movement repeats in a loop: collect all units, attempt moves, apply changes. The loop continues until a full pass produces zero moves. This stabilizes positions when units block each other.

---

## Attack

After movement, each unit attacks one enemy in range.

### Target Selection

Scan all cells within manhattan distance of the unit's attack range. For each occupied cell containing an enemy unit, evaluate as a candidate target.

**Priority (in order):**
1. Lowest health (focus fire on wounded targets)
2. Closest distance (prefer nearby enemies)
3. Closest to map center
4. Lowest entity ID (stable tiebreak)

### Damage

Subtract the attacker's damage from the target's health. Health can go negative ‚ÄĒ the despawn system removes dead units after all attacks resolve.

Add the TookDamage marker to the target. This marker is used for rendering (damage flash) and is cleared at the start of the next turn.

### Simultaneous Resolution

All units attack in a single pass. A unit can be killed by an earlier attacker and still attack in the same turn (it is not removed until the despawn phase). However, units are processed in entity_id order, so the sequence is deterministic.

---

## Death and Despawn

After all attacks resolve, the despawn system removes units with health <= 0.

Dead units are collected into an array during iteration, then deleted after the query finishes. This avoids modifying the ECS world during iteration.

---

## Win Conditions

After despawn, the app_stop system checks both factions:

| Condition | Result |
|-----------|--------|
| No living red units (health > 0) | Knights Win |
| No living blue units (health > 0) | Archers Win |
| Both factions eliminated simultaneously | Knights Win (checked first) |
| Turn limit reached (1000) | No winner declared |

---

## Distance

All distance calculations use **manhattan distance**: `|x1 - x2| + |y1 - y2|`.

This applies to attack range, movement scoring, target selection priority, and centrality tiebreaking.

---

## Spatial Grid

A static 2D occupancy grid tracks unit positions for O(1) lookups:
- Dimensions: 512 x 256 (maximum supported map size)
- Each cell stores unit index + 1 (0 = empty)
- Rebuilt each movement phase
- Out-of-bounds cells return occupied

---

## Balance

The game's balance depends on the tension between archer range advantage and knight health advantage.

| Lever | Archer | Knight | Ratio |
|-------|--------|--------|-------|
| Count | 1127 | 2649 | 1 : 2.3 |
| Health | 10 | 35 | 1 : 3.5 |
| Damage | 5 | 5 | 1 : 1 |
| Range | 3 | 1 | 3 : 1 |

Knights need to close distance before archers whittle them down. Archers need enough space to kite. The 320-wide map gives archers room to maneuver; the 2.3:1 knight numerical advantage compensates.

Tuning levers in app.yaml: army sizes, map dimensions, max turns. Tuning levers in entity prefabs: health, damage, range, movement type.

---

## Implementation Notes

### Determinism

The simulation is fully deterministic given the same RNG seed. No randomness exists after spawning. Units are sorted by entity_id before processing, ensuring consistent iteration order.

### Buffer Sizes

All stack arrays in native systems must accommodate the maximum unit count. The current maximum is 4096 units. Undersized buffers silently drop units, causing non-determinism.

### Movement Speed

Speed must always be 1. The movement loop assumes each unit moves at most once per pass. Speed > 1 causes infinite oscillation as units unblock each other repeatedly.

### Per-Turn Flags

TookDamage is a marker component used as a per-turn signal. It is added by the attack system and removed by start_of_turn. Use `ecs_remove_id` to clear it ‚ÄĒ setting a bool field to false leaves the component present in queries, causing ghost state.
name: Archer
abstract: true
components:
  Health: { base: 10 }
  MovementSpeed: { base: 1, energy: 0 }
  MovementType: kite
  Weapon: { range: 3 }
  AttackDamage: { base: 5 }
  RedFaction: true
name: Knight
abstract: true
components:
  Health: { base: 25 }
  MovementSpeed: { base: 1, energy: 0 }
  MovementType: charge
  Weapon: { range: 1 }
  AttackDamage: { base: 5 }
  BlueFaction: true
#include "systems.h"
#include "engine/systems.h"
#include "engine/components.h"
#include "engine/templates.h"
#include "engine/history.h"
#include "engine/app.h"
#include <stdlib.h>
#include <stdio.h>
#include <string.h>
#include <math.h>
#include <time.h>

/* ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ Helpers ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ */

typedef struct {
    ecs_entity_t eid;
    int entity_id;
    int x, y;
    int health;
    int speed, energy;
    int range, damage;
    int faction;  /* enum index: 0=red, 1=blue */
    int move_type; /* enum index: 0=kite, 1=charge */
} UnitData;

static int manhattan(int x1, int y1, int x2, int y2) {
    return abs(x1 - x2) + abs(y1 - y2);
}

/* Collect living units from query into array, return count */
static int collect_units(Engine *engine, UnitData *units, int max_units) {
    ecs_entity_t loc_comp = ecs_lookup(engine->world, "Location");
    ecs_entity_t hp_comp = ecs_lookup(engine->world, "Health");
    ecs_entity_t spd_comp = ecs_lookup(engine->world, "MovementSpeed");
    ecs_entity_t rng_comp = ecs_lookup(engine->world, "Weapon");
    ecs_entity_t dmg_comp = ecs_lookup(engine->world, "AttackDamage");
    ecs_entity_t red_comp = ecs_lookup(engine->world, "RedFaction");
    ecs_entity_t blue_comp = ecs_lookup(engine->world, "BlueFaction");
    ecs_entity_t mt_comp = ecs_lookup(engine->world, "MovementType");

    if (!loc_comp || !hp_comp) return 0;

    ecs_query_t *q = ecs_query(engine->world, {
        .terms = {
            { .id = loc_comp },
            { .id = hp_comp },
            { .id = engine->user_entity_tag },
        },
        .cache_kind = EcsQueryCacheNone
    });

    int count = 0;
    ecs_iter_t it = ecs_query_iter(engine->world, q);
    while (ecs_query_next(&it)) {
        for (int i = 0; i < it.count && count < max_units; i++) {
            ecs_entity_t eid = it.entities[i];

            /* Read Health */
            const int32_t *hp = (const int32_t *)ecs_get_id(engine->world, eid, hp_comp);
            if (!hp || *hp <= 0) continue;

            UnitData *u = &units[count];
            u->eid = eid;
            u->health = *hp;

            /* EntityId */
            const int32_t *eid_val = (const int32_t *)ecs_get_id(engine->world, eid, engine->entity_id_comp);
            u->entity_id = eid_val ? *eid_val : 0;

            /* Location */
            const void *loc_data = ecs_get_id(engine->world, eid, loc_comp);
            if (loc_data) {
                u->x = *(const int32_t *)loc_data;
                u->y = *((const int32_t *)loc_data + 1);
            }
            /* MovementSpeed */
            if (spd_comp && ecs_has_id(engine->world, eid, spd_comp)) {
                const void *spd_data = ecs_get_id(engine->world, eid, spd_comp);
                if (spd_data) {
                    u->speed = *(const int32_t *)spd_data;
                    u->energy = u->speed;
                }
            }

            /* Weapon (range is first field) */
            if (rng_comp && ecs_has_id(engine->world, eid, rng_comp)) {
                const int32_t *r = (const int32_t *)ecs_get_id(engine->world, eid, rng_comp);
                if (r) u->range = *r;
            }

            /* AttackDamage */
            if (dmg_comp && ecs_has_id(engine->world, eid, dmg_comp)) {
                const int32_t *d = (const int32_t *)ecs_get_id(engine->world, eid, dmg_comp);
                if (d) u->damage = *d;
            }

            /* Faction (marker components) */
            if (red_comp && ecs_has_id(engine->world, eid, red_comp))
                u->faction = 0; /* red */
            else if (blue_comp && ecs_has_id(engine->world, eid, blue_comp))
                u->faction = 1; /* blue */

            /* MovementType (enum) */
            if (mt_comp && ecs_has_id(engine->world, eid, mt_comp)) {
                const int32_t *m = (const int32_t *)ecs_get_id(engine->world, eid, mt_comp);
                if (m) u->move_type = *m;
            }

            count++;
        }
    }
    ecs_query_fini(q);

    /* Sort by entity_id */
    for (int i = 0; i < count - 1; i++)
        for (int j = i + 1; j < count; j++)
            if (units[j].entity_id < units[i].entity_id) {
                UnitData tmp = units[i]; units[i] = units[j]; units[j] = tmp;
            }

    return count;
}

/* ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ Helper: ensure TookDamage component exists ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ */

static ecs_entity_t ensure_took_damage_comp(Engine *engine) {
    ecs_entity_t td = ecs_lookup(engine->world, "TookDamage");
    if (td) return td;

    /* Register it */
    td = ecs_entity(engine->world, { .name = "TookDamage" });
    ecs_set(engine->world, td, EcsComponent, {
        .size = sizeof(ecs_bool_t), .alignment = ECS_ALIGNOF(ecs_bool_t)
    });
    ecs_struct(engine->world, {
        .entity = td,
        .members = {{ .name = "value", .type = ecs_id(ecs_bool_t) }}
    });
    return td;
}

/* ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ Spatial grid for O(1) occupancy lookups ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ */

#define GRID_MAX_X 512
#define GRID_MAX_Y 256
static int16_t g_occ_grid[GRID_MAX_X * GRID_MAX_Y]; /* unit index+1, 0=empty */

static void grid_clear(int mx, int my) {
    (void)mx; (void)my;
    memset(g_occ_grid, 0, sizeof(g_occ_grid));
}

static void grid_set(int x, int y, int unit_idx) {
    if (x >= 1 && x < GRID_MAX_X && y >= 1 && y < GRID_MAX_Y)
        g_occ_grid[y * GRID_MAX_X + x] = (int16_t)(unit_idx + 1);
}

static bool grid_occupied(int x, int y) {
    if (x < 1 || x >= GRID_MAX_X || y < 1 || y >= GRID_MAX_Y) return true;
    return g_occ_grid[y * GRID_MAX_X + x] != 0;
}

static int grid_unit_at(int x, int y) {
    if (x < 1 || x >= GRID_MAX_X || y < 1 || y >= GRID_MAX_Y) return -1;
    return g_occ_grid[y * GRID_MAX_X + x] - 1;
}

/* ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ start_of_turn ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ */

static void avk_start_of_turn(Engine *engine) {
    if (is_simulation_paused(engine)) return;
    ecs_entity_t td = ecs_lookup(engine->world, "TookDamage");
    ecs_entity_t wpn_comp = ecs_lookup(engine->world, "Weapon");

    /* Clear TookDamage markers */
    if (td) {
        ecs_entity_t to_clear[4096];
        int clear_count = 0;

        ecs_query_t *q = ecs_query(engine->world, {
            .terms = {{ .id = td }, { .id = engine->user_entity_tag }},
            .cache_kind = EcsQueryCacheNone
        });
        ecs_iter_t it = ecs_query_iter(engine->world, q);
        while (ecs_query_next(&it)) {
            for (int i = 0; i < it.count && clear_count < 4096; i++) {
                to_clear[clear_count++] = it.entities[i];
            }
        }
        ecs_query_fini(q);

        for (int i = 0; i < clear_count; i++) {
            ecs_remove_id(engine->world, to_clear[i], td);
        }
    }

    /* Clear Weapon.attacked field (set to 0) */
    if (wpn_comp) {
        ecs_query_t *q = ecs_query(engine->world, {
            .terms = {{ .id = wpn_comp }, { .id = engine->user_entity_tag }},
            .cache_kind = EcsQueryCacheNone
        });
        ecs_iter_t it = ecs_query_iter(engine->world, q);
        while (ecs_query_next(&it)) {
            for (int i = 0; i < it.count; i++) {
                void *wpn = ecs_get_mut_id(engine->world, it.entities[i], wpn_comp);
                if (wpn) {
                    ecs_entity_t *attacked = (ecs_entity_t *)((char *)wpn + sizeof(int32_t));
                    *attacked = 0;
                    ecs_modified_id(engine->world, it.entities[i], wpn_comp);
                }
            }
        }
        ecs_query_fini(q);
    }
}

/* ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ game_start ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ */

static void avk_app_start(Engine *engine) {
    /* Find Map entity for bounds */
    ecs_entity_t map = ecs_lookup(engine->world, "Map");
    if (!map) return;

    ecs_entity_t ms_comp = ecs_lookup(engine->world, "MapSize");
    if (!ms_comp) return;
    const void *ms_data = ecs_get_id(engine->world, map, ms_comp);
    if (!ms_data) return;
    int mx = *(const int32_t *)ms_data;
    int my = *((const int32_t *)ms_data + 1);
    if (mx == 0 && my == 0) return;

    { static int seed_offset = 0; srand((unsigned)time(NULL) + seed_offset++); }

    ecs_entity_t sr_comp = ecs_lookup(engine->world, "SpawnRequest");
    ecs_entity_t loc_comp = ecs_lookup(engine->world, "Location");
    if (!sr_comp || !loc_comp) return;

    /* Read unit counts from app.yaml (use --overrides for balance testing) */
    StoredApp *app = engine_app_get(engine, engine->sandbox_name);
    if (!app || app->archers <= 0 || app->knights <= 0) {
        fprintf(stderr, "Error: archers/knights not set in app.yaml\n");
        return;
    }
    int num_archers = app->archers;
    int num_knights = app->knights;

    int total = num_archers + num_knights;
    int cells = mx * my;
    if (total > cells) {
        fprintf(stderr, "Error: %d units > %d cells, can't place without overlap\n", total, cells);
        return;
    }

    fprintf(stderr, "Spawning %dA vs %dK\n", num_archers, num_knights);

    /* Placement grid to prevent overlaps */
    grid_clear(mx, my);

    /* knights */
    for (int k = 0; k < num_knights; k++) {
        char name[32]; snprintf(name, sizeof(name), "sk%d", k + 1);
        ecs_entity_t e = engine_entity_create(engine, name);
        if (!e) continue;
        ecs_add_id(engine->world, e, sr_comp);
        void *sr = ecs_get_mut_id(engine->world, e, sr_comp);
        if (sr) { *(char **)sr = ecs_os_strdup("Knight"); ecs_modified_id(engine->world, e, sr_comp); }

        int px, py;
        do { px = 1 + rand() % mx; py = 1 + rand() % my; } while (grid_occupied(px, py));
        grid_set(px, py, 1);

        ecs_add_id(engine->world, e, loc_comp);
        int32_t *loc = (int32_t *)ecs_get_mut_id(engine->world, e, loc_comp);
        if (loc) { loc[0] = px; loc[1] = py; ecs_modified_id(engine->world, e, loc_comp); }
    }

    /* archers */
    for (int a = 0; a < num_archers; a++) {
        char name[32]; snprintf(name, sizeof(name), "sa%d", a + 1);
        ecs_entity_t e = engine_entity_create(engine, name);
        if (!e) continue;
        ecs_add_id(engine->world, e, sr_comp);
        void *sr = ecs_get_mut_id(engine->world, e, sr_comp);
        if (sr) { *(char **)sr = ecs_os_strdup("Archer"); ecs_modified_id(engine->world, e, sr_comp); }

        int px, py;
        do { px = 1 + rand() % mx; py = 1 + rand() % my; } while (grid_occupied(px, py));
        grid_set(px, py, 1);

        ecs_add_id(engine->world, e, loc_comp);
        int32_t *loc = (int32_t *)ecs_get_mut_id(engine->world, e, loc_comp);
        if (loc) { loc[0] = px; loc[1] = py; ecs_modified_id(engine->world, e, loc_comp); }
    }

    engine_system_disable(engine, "app_start");
}

/* ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ BFS distance fields ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ */
/*
 * dist_to_red[y][x] = manhattan distance to nearest red (archer) unit
 * dist_to_blue[y][x] = manhattan distance to nearest blue (knight) unit
 * Built via BFS flood-fill from all enemy positions: O(cells) not O(units¬≤).
 * A cell with distance 0 contains an enemy ‚ÄĒ the movement target and attack condition.
 *
 * Owner arrays track which unit index "owns" each cell (nearest source).
 * Used by incremental_update to walk Voronoi regions efficiently.
 */

static int16_t g_dist_to_red[GRID_MAX_Y * GRID_MAX_X];
static int16_t g_dist_to_blue[GRID_MAX_Y * GRID_MAX_X];
static int16_t g_owner_red[GRID_MAX_Y * GRID_MAX_X];
static int16_t g_owner_blue[GRID_MAX_Y * GRID_MAX_X];

/* BFS queue ‚ÄĒ max cells = GRID_MAX_X * GRID_MAX_Y */
#define BFS_MAX (GRID_MAX_X * GRID_MAX_Y)
static int32_t g_bfs_queue[BFS_MAX];

/* Bitset for incremental update phases */
#define BITSET_SIZE ((GRID_MAX_X * GRID_MAX_Y + 63) / 64)
static uint64_t g_raised[BITSET_SIZE];
static uint64_t g_in_queue[BITSET_SIZE];

static inline void bit_set(uint64_t *bs, int idx) { bs[idx/64] |= (1ULL << (idx%64)); }
static inline void bit_clear(uint64_t *bs, int idx) { (void)bs; (void)idx; bs[idx/64] &= ~(1ULL << (idx%64)); }
static inline bool bit_test(uint64_t *bs, int idx) { return (bs[idx/64] >> (idx%64)) & 1; }

typedef struct { int unit_idx; int old_x, old_y, new_x, new_y; } MovedSite;

/* Scratch buffer to collect raised cell indices during phase 1 */
static int32_t g_raised_cells[BFS_MAX];

static void build_distance_field(int16_t *dist, int16_t *owner, UnitData *units,
                                 int count, int faction, int mx, int my) {
    /* Coordinates are 1-based: valid range is 1..mx, 1..my */
    /* Init all to -1 (unvisited) ‚ÄĒ 0xFF bytes produce -1 in int16 two's complement */
    memset(dist, 0xFF, (size_t)(my + 1) * GRID_MAX_X * sizeof(int16_t));
    memset(owner, 0xFF, (size_t)(my + 1) * GRID_MAX_X * sizeof(int16_t));

    /* Seed BFS with all units of the target faction */
    int head = 0, tail = 0;
    for (int i = 0; i < count; i++) {
        if (units[i].faction != faction) continue;
        int x = units[i].x, y = units[i].y;
        if (x >= 1 && x <= mx && y >= 1 && y <= my && dist[y * GRID_MAX_X + x] < 0) {
            dist[y * GRID_MAX_X + x] = 0;
            owner[y * GRID_MAX_X + x] = (int16_t)i;
            g_bfs_queue[tail++] = y * (mx + 1) + x;
        }
    }

    /* BFS flood fill ‚ÄĒ propagate owner along with distance */
    static const int dx[] = {0, 0, -1, 1};
    static const int dy[] = {-1, 1, 0, 0};
    while (head < tail) {
        int pos = g_bfs_queue[head++];
        int cy = pos / (mx + 1), cx = pos % (mx + 1);
        int16_t d = dist[cy * GRID_MAX_X + cx];
        int16_t o = owner[cy * GRID_MAX_X + cx];
        for (int dir = 0; dir < 4; dir++) {
            int nx = cx + dx[dir], ny = cy + dy[dir];
            if (nx < 1 || nx > mx || ny < 1 || ny > my) continue;
            int ni = ny * GRID_MAX_X + nx;
            if (dist[ni] >= 0) continue;
            dist[ni] = d + 1;
            owner[ni] = o;
            g_bfs_queue[tail++] = ny * (mx + 1) + nx;
        }
    }
}

/* ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ Incremental distance field update ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ */
/*
 * When a small number of sites (units) move, we can update the distance
 * field incrementally instead of doing a full BFS rebuild:
 *
 * Phase 1: For each moved site, walk its Voronoi region (cells owned by it)
 *   from the old position. Recompute distances using manhattan distance to the
 *   new position. Mark cells where distance increased as "raised".
 *
 * Phase 2: BFS repair from (a) new positions of moved sites and
 *   (b) non-raised neighbors of raised cells. This corrects any cells
 *   that should now be owned by a different (closer) site.
 */
static void incremental_update(int16_t *dist, int16_t *own,
                               MovedSite *moved, int nmoved,
                               UnitData *units, int mx, int my) {
    (void)units;
    static const int dx[] = {0, 0, -1, 1};
    static const int dy[] = {-1, 1, 0, 0};
    int W = GRID_MAX_X;

    /* Clear bitsets (only the portion we use) */
    size_t bitset_bytes = ((size_t)(my + 1) * W + 63) / 64 * sizeof(uint64_t);
    if (bitset_bytes > sizeof(g_raised)) bitset_bytes = sizeof(g_raised);
    memset(g_raised, 0, bitset_bytes);
    memset(g_in_queue, 0, bitset_bytes);

    int n_raised = 0;

    /* PHASE 1: Walk each moved site's Voronoi region, update distances.
     *
     * Two-pass per site:
     *   Pass A: BFS to collect all cells in this site's Voronoi region.
     *           Keep visited markers in place to prevent revisiting.
     *   Pass B: Iterate collected cells, compute new manhattan distance
     *           to the site's new position, mark raised cells, restore owner. */
    for (int m = 0; m < nmoved; m++) {
        int sid = moved[m].unit_idx;
        int ox = moved[m].old_x, oy = moved[m].old_y;
        int nx = moved[m].new_x, ny = moved[m].new_y;

        int16_t visited_mark = (int16_t)(-2 - sid);

        /* Pass A: BFS to collect Voronoi cells */
        int head = 0, tail = 0;
        int oi = oy * W + ox;

        if (own[oi] == (int16_t)sid) {
            own[oi] = visited_mark;
            g_bfs_queue[tail++] = oi;
        }

        /* The BFS only enqueues cells once (via visited_mark), so tail <= total cells */
        while (head < tail) {
            int ci = g_bfs_queue[head++];
            int cy = ci / W, cx = ci % W;

            for (int dir = 0; dir < 4; dir++) {
                int ex = cx + dx[dir], ey = cy + dy[dir];
                if (ex < 1 || ex > mx || ey < 1 || ey > my) continue;
                int ei = ey * W + ex;
                if (own[ei] == (int16_t)sid) {
                    own[ei] = visited_mark;
                    g_bfs_queue[tail++] = ei;
                }
            }
        }

        /* Pass B: Update distances and restore owners for collected cells.
         * g_bfs_queue[0..tail-1] contains all cells in this site's Voronoi region. */
        for (int k = 0; k < tail; k++) {
            int ci = g_bfs_queue[k];
            int cy = ci / W, cx = ci % W;

            int new_d = abs(cx - nx) + abs(cy - ny);
            if (new_d > dist[ci]) {
                bit_set(g_raised, ci);
                g_raised_cells[n_raised++] = ci;
            }
            dist[ci] = (int16_t)new_d;
            own[ci] = (int16_t)sid; /* restore owner */
        }
    }

    /* PHASE 2: Repair ‚ÄĒ BFS from boundary of raised region + new site positions */
    int head = 0, tail = 0;

    /* Seed (a): new positions of moved sites */
    for (int m = 0; m < nmoved; m++) {
        int ni = moved[m].new_y * W + moved[m].new_x;
        dist[ni] = 0;
        own[ni] = (int16_t)moved[m].unit_idx;
        if (!bit_test(g_in_queue, ni)) {
            g_bfs_queue[tail++] = ni;
            bit_set(g_in_queue, ni);
        }
    }

    /* Seed (b): non-raised neighbors of raised cells (using collected list) */
    for (int r = 0; r < n_raised; r++) {
        int ci = g_raised_cells[r];
        int cy = ci / W, cx = ci % W;
        for (int dir = 0; dir < 4; dir++) {
            int ex = cx + dx[dir], ey = cy + dy[dir];
            if (ex < 1 || ex > mx || ey < 1 || ey > my) continue;
            int ei = ey * W + ex;
            if (!bit_test(g_raised, ei) && !bit_test(g_in_queue, ei)) {
                g_bfs_queue[tail++] = ei;
                bit_set(g_in_queue, ei);
            }
        }
    }

    /* BFS repair */
    while (head < tail) {
        int ci = g_bfs_queue[head++];
        int cy = ci / W, cx = ci % W;
        for (int dir = 0; dir < 4; dir++) {
            int ex = cx + dx[dir], ey = cy + dy[dir];
            if (ex < 1 || ex > mx || ey < 1 || ey > my) continue;
            int ei = ey * W + ex;
            if (dist[ci] + 1 < dist[ei]) {
                dist[ei] = dist[ci] + 1;
                own[ei] = own[ci];
                if (!bit_test(g_in_queue, ei)) {
                    g_bfs_queue[tail++] = ei;
                    bit_set(g_in_queue, ei);
                }
            }
        }
    }
}

static int dist_field_get(int16_t *dist, int x, int y) {
    if (x < 1 || x >= GRID_MAX_X || y < 1 || y >= GRID_MAX_Y) return 9999;
    int16_t v = dist[y * GRID_MAX_X + x];
    return v >= 0 ? v : 9999;
}

/* Count enemies within manhattan range of (cx,cy) using the occupancy grid */
static int count_enemies_in_range(int cx, int cy, int range, int my_faction,
                                  UnitData *units) {
    int count = 0;
    for (int dy = -range; dy <= range; dy++) {
        int ax = range - abs(dy);
        for (int dx = -ax; dx <= ax; dx++) {
            int ui = grid_unit_at(cx + dx, cy + dy);
            if (ui >= 0 && units[ui].faction != my_faction && units[ui].health > 0)
                count++;
        }
    }
    return count;
}

/* Score a cell for movement using distance fields + grid */
static int score_cell(int nx, int ny, int move_type, int range,
                      int16_t *enemy_dist, int faction, UnitData *units) {
    int d = dist_field_get(enemy_dist, nx, ny);
    if (move_type == 1) {
        /* Knight: minimize distance to nearest enemy */
        return -d;
    } else {
        /* Archer: prefer being at exactly range distance */
        if (d <= range)
            return -(range - d + 1);  /* dist 1=-3, 2=-2, 3=-1 */
        else
            return -d;                /* dist 4=-4, 5=-5, ... */
    }
}

/* ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ movement ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ */

static void avk_movement(Engine *engine) {
    if (is_simulation_paused(engine)) return;
    ecs_entity_t map = ecs_lookup(engine->world, "Map");
    ecs_entity_t ms_comp = ecs_lookup(engine->world, "MapSize");
    int mx = 10, my = 10;
    if (map && ms_comp) {
        const void *ms = ecs_get_id(engine->world, map, ms_comp);
        if (ms) { mx = *(const int32_t *)ms; my = *((const int32_t *)ms + 1); }
    }

    UnitData units[4096];
    int count = collect_units(engine, units, 4096);
    if (count == 0) return;

    ecs_entity_t loc_comp = ecs_lookup(engine->world, "Location");

    /* Set energy */
    for (int i = 0; i < count; i++) units[i].energy = units[i].speed;

    /* Build spatial grid */
    grid_clear(mx, my);
    for (int i = 0; i < count; i++)
        grid_set(units[i].x, units[i].y, i);

    static const int dirs[][2] = {{0,-1},{0,1},{-1,0},{1,0},{0,0}};

    /* Debug logging */
    static FILE *dbg = NULL;
    static int dbg_checked = 0;
    if (!dbg_checked) {
        dbg_checked = 1;
        const char *dbg_path = getenv("FLECS_DEBUG_MOVEMENT");
        if (dbg_path) {
            dbg = fopen(dbg_path, "w");
            if (dbg) { fprintf(dbg, "debug enabled\n"); fflush(dbg); }
        }
    }
    static int dbg_turn = 0;
    dbg_turn++;

    /* Pending moves buffer ‚ÄĒ applied in batch after each pass */
    int pend_idx[4096], pend_x[4096], pend_y[4096];

    /* MovedSite buffers for incremental update */
    MovedSite moved_red[4096], moved_blue[4096];

    /* Adaptive threshold: use incremental only when few units moved.
     * Incremental cost = O(voronoi_region_sum) + O(repair_bfs).
     * Full rebuild cost = O(cells).
     * When many units move, the voronoi walk alone approaches O(cells)
     * and the repair adds more, making full rebuild cheaper. */
    int incr_threshold = count / 8;
    if (incr_threshold < 32) incr_threshold = 32;

    /* Build initial distance fields with owner tracking (full BFS) */
    build_distance_field(g_dist_to_red, g_owner_red, units, count, 0, mx, my);
    build_distance_field(g_dist_to_blue, g_owner_blue, units, count, 1, mx, my);

    bool any_moved = true;
    while (any_moved) {
        any_moved = false;

        /* Phase 1: decide moves for all units */
        int npend = 0;
        for (int i = 0; i < count; i++) {
            UnitData *ent = &units[i];
            if (ent->energy <= 0) continue;

            /* Enemy distance field for this unit */
            int16_t *enemy_dist = (ent->faction == 0) ? g_dist_to_blue : g_dist_to_red;

            /* Collect candidates with scores ‚ÄĒ O(1) per direction via distance field */
            int cand_x[5], cand_y[5], cand_score[5], ncand = 0;
            int best_score = -999999;

            for (int d = 0; d < 5; d++) {
                int nx = ent->x + dirs[d][0];
                int ny = ent->y + dirs[d][1];

                if (nx < 1 || nx > mx || ny < 1 || ny > my) continue;
                if (d != 4 && grid_occupied(nx, ny)) continue;

                int score = score_cell(nx, ny, ent->move_type, ent->range,
                                       enemy_dist, ent->faction, units);

                cand_x[ncand] = nx;
                cand_y[ncand] = ny;
                cand_score[ncand] = score;
                ncand++;
                if (score > best_score) best_score = score;
            }

            /* Tiebreaker 1 (knights): prefer backed by ally ‚ÄĒ O(1) grid check */
            int best_backed = 0;
            if (ent->move_type == 1) {
                for (int c = 0; c < ncand; c++) {
                    if (cand_score[c] != best_score) continue;
                    int bk_x = 2 * ent->x - cand_x[c];
                    int bk_y = 2 * ent->y - cand_y[c];
                    int ally = grid_unit_at(bk_x, bk_y);
                    if (ally >= 0 && ally != i && units[ally].faction == ent->faction) {
                        best_backed = 1; break;
                    }
                }
            }

            /* Tiebreaker 2: farthest from nearest wall */
            int best_wdist = -1;
            for (int c = 0; c < ncand; c++) {
                if (cand_score[c] != best_score) continue;
                if (ent->move_type == 1 && best_backed) {
                    int bk_x = 2 * ent->x - cand_x[c];
                    int bk_y = 2 * ent->y - cand_y[c];
                    int ally = grid_unit_at(bk_x, bk_y);
                    if (!(ally >= 0 && ally != i && units[ally].faction == ent->faction))
                        continue;
                }
                int wx = cand_x[c] - 1 < mx - cand_x[c] ? cand_x[c] - 1 : mx - cand_x[c];
                int wy = cand_y[c] - 1 < my - cand_y[c] ? cand_y[c] - 1 : my - cand_y[c];
                int wd = wx < wy ? wx : wy;
                if (wd > best_wdist) best_wdist = wd;
            }

            /* Tiebreaker 3: prefer reducing the larger axis to target enemy */
            int16_t *enemy_own = (ent->faction == 0) ? g_owner_blue : g_owner_red;
            int tgt_idx = enemy_own[ent->y * GRID_MAX_X + ent->x];
            int best_axis = 0;
            if (tgt_idx >= 0 && tgt_idx < count) {
                int tx = units[tgt_idx].x, ty = units[tgt_idx].y;
                int adx = abs(ent->x - tx), ady = abs(ent->y - ty);
                if (adx != ady) {
                    for (int c = 0; c < ncand; c++) {
                        if (cand_score[c] != best_score) continue;
                        if (ent->move_type == 1 && best_backed) {
                            int bk_x = 2 * ent->x - cand_x[c];
                            int bk_y = 2 * ent->y - cand_y[c];
                            int ally = grid_unit_at(bk_x, bk_y);
                            if (!(ally >= 0 && ally != i && units[ally].faction == ent->faction))
                                continue;
                        }
                        int wx = cand_x[c] - 1 < mx - cand_x[c] ? cand_x[c] - 1 : mx - cand_x[c];
                        int wy = cand_y[c] - 1 < my - cand_y[c] ? cand_y[c] - 1 : my - cand_y[c];
                        int wd = wx < wy ? wx : wy;
                        if (wd != best_wdist) continue;
                        int pref = (adx >= ady)
                            ? (abs(cand_x[c] - tx) < adx)
                            : (abs(cand_y[c] - ty) < ady);
                        if (pref > best_axis) best_axis = pref;
                    }
                }
            }

            /* Pick first matching candidate */
            int bx = ent->x, by = ent->y;
            bool found = false;
            for (int c = 0; c < ncand; c++) {
                if (cand_score[c] != best_score) continue;
                if (ent->move_type == 1 && best_backed) {
                    int bk_x = 2 * ent->x - cand_x[c];
                    int bk_y = 2 * ent->y - cand_y[c];
                    int ally = grid_unit_at(bk_x, bk_y);
                    if (!(ally >= 0 && ally != i && units[ally].faction == ent->faction))
                        continue;
                }
                int wx = cand_x[c] - 1 < mx - cand_x[c] ? cand_x[c] - 1 : mx - cand_x[c];
                int wy = cand_y[c] - 1 < my - cand_y[c] ? cand_y[c] - 1 : my - cand_y[c];
                int wd = wx < wy ? wx : wy;
                if (wd != best_wdist) continue;
                if (best_axis && tgt_idx >= 0 && tgt_idx < count) {
                    int tx = units[tgt_idx].x, ty = units[tgt_idx].y;
                    int adx = abs(ent->x - tx), ady = abs(ent->y - ty);
                    int pref = (adx >= ady)
                        ? (abs(cand_x[c] - tx) < adx)
                        : (abs(cand_y[c] - ty) < ady);
                    if (!pref) continue;
                }
                bx = cand_x[c]; by = cand_y[c];
                found = true;
                break;
            }

            /* Debug: log decision */
            if (dbg) {
                const char *type = ent->faction == 0 ? "Archer" : "Knight";
                fprintf(dbg, "turn:%d %s at(%d,%d) best_score:%d candidates:",
                        dbg_turn, type, ent->x, ent->y, best_score);
                for (int c = 0; c < ncand; c++) {
                    int wx2 = cand_x[c] - 1 < mx - cand_x[c] ? cand_x[c] - 1 : mx - cand_x[c];
                    int wy2 = cand_y[c] - 1 < my - cand_y[c] ? cand_y[c] - 1 : my - cand_y[c];
                    int wd2 = wx2 < wy2 ? wx2 : wy2;
                    fprintf(dbg, " (%d,%d)s=%d,w=%d%s",
                            cand_x[c], cand_y[c], cand_score[c], wd2,
                            (cand_score[c] == best_score) ? "*" : "");
                }
                fprintf(dbg, " -> (%d,%d)\n", bx, by);
                fflush(dbg);
            }

            if (found && (bx != ent->x || by != ent->y)) {
                pend_idx[npend] = i;
                pend_x[npend] = bx;
                pend_y[npend] = by;
                npend++;
            } else if (!found) {
                ent->energy = 0;
            }
        }

        /* Phase 2: apply moves, skip if target now occupied.
         * Track which faction's units actually moved for incremental update. */
        int n_moved_red = 0, n_moved_blue = 0;

        for (int p = 0; p < npend; p++) {
            int i = pend_idx[p];
            UnitData *ent = &units[i];
            if (grid_occupied(pend_x[p], pend_y[p])) continue;

            int old_x = ent->x, old_y = ent->y;
            g_occ_grid[ent->y * GRID_MAX_X + ent->x] = 0;
            ent->x = pend_x[p]; ent->y = pend_y[p];
            grid_set(ent->x, ent->y, i);
            ent->energy--;

            int32_t *loc = (int32_t *)ecs_get_mut_id(engine->world, ent->eid, loc_comp);
            if (loc) { loc[0] = ent->x; loc[1] = ent->y; ecs_modified_id(engine->world, ent->eid, loc_comp); }
            any_moved = true;

            /* Record movement by faction for distance field update */
            if (ent->faction == 0) {
                moved_red[n_moved_red].unit_idx = i;
                moved_red[n_moved_red].old_x = old_x;
                moved_red[n_moved_red].old_y = old_y;
                moved_red[n_moved_red].new_x = ent->x;
                moved_red[n_moved_red].new_y = ent->y;
                n_moved_red++;
            } else {
                moved_blue[n_moved_blue].unit_idx = i;
                moved_blue[n_moved_blue].old_x = old_x;
                moved_blue[n_moved_blue].old_y = old_y;
                moved_blue[n_moved_blue].new_x = ent->x;
                moved_blue[n_moved_blue].new_y = ent->y;
                n_moved_blue++;
            }
        }

        /* Phase 3: Update distance fields ‚ÄĒ incremental if few moved, else full rebuild */
        if (any_moved) {
            if (n_moved_red > 0) {
                if (n_moved_red > incr_threshold) {
                    build_distance_field(g_dist_to_red, g_owner_red, units, count, 0, mx, my);
                } else {
                    incremental_update(g_dist_to_red, g_owner_red, moved_red, n_moved_red, units, mx, my);
                }
            }
            if (n_moved_blue > 0) {
                if (n_moved_blue > incr_threshold) {
                    build_distance_field(g_dist_to_blue, g_owner_blue, units, count, 1, mx, my);
                } else {
                    incremental_update(g_dist_to_blue, g_owner_blue, moved_blue, n_moved_blue, units, mx, my);
                }
            }
        }

    }
}

/* ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ attack ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ */

static void avk_attack(Engine *engine) {
    if (is_simulation_paused(engine)) return;
    UnitData units[4096];
    int count = collect_units(engine, units, 4096);

    ecs_entity_t hp_comp = ecs_lookup(engine->world, "Health");
    ecs_entity_t wpn_comp = ecs_lookup(engine->world, "Weapon");
    ecs_entity_t td_comp = ensure_took_damage_comp(engine);
    if (!hp_comp) return;

    /* Get map bounds for center tiebreaking */
    ecs_entity_t map_ent = ecs_lookup(engine->world, "Map");
    ecs_entity_t ms_comp = ecs_lookup(engine->world, "MapSize");
    int mx = 320, my = 144;
    if (map_ent && ms_comp) {
        const void *ms = ecs_get_id(engine->world, map_ent, ms_comp);
        if (ms) { mx = *(const int32_t *)ms; my = *((const int32_t *)ms + 1); }
    }
    int cx = mx / 2, cy = my / 2;

    /* Build occupancy grid if not already built by movement */
    grid_clear(mx, my);
    for (int i = 0; i < count; i++)
        grid_set(units[i].x, units[i].y, i);

    for (int i = 0; i < count; i++) {
        if (units[i].health <= 0) continue;
        int range = units[i].range;

        UnitData *target = NULL;
        int target_dist = 999999;
        int target_cdist = 999999;

        for (int dy = -range; dy <= range; dy++) {
            int ax = range - abs(dy);
            for (int dx = -ax; dx <= ax; dx++) {
                int tx = units[i].x + dx;
                int ty = units[i].y + dy;
                int ui = grid_unit_at(tx, ty);
                if (ui < 0) continue;
                if (units[ui].health <= 0 || units[ui].faction == units[i].faction) continue;

                int dist = abs(dx) + abs(dy);
                int cdist = abs(tx - cx) + abs(ty - cy);
                if (!target ||
                    units[ui].health < target->health ||
                    (units[ui].health == target->health && dist < target_dist) ||
                    (units[ui].health == target->health && dist == target_dist && cdist < target_cdist) ||
                    (units[ui].health == target->health && dist == target_dist && cdist == target_cdist && units[ui].entity_id < target->entity_id)) {
                    target = &units[ui];
                    target_dist = dist;
                    target_cdist = cdist;
                }
            }
        }

        if (target) {
            target->health -= units[i].damage;
            int32_t *hp = (int32_t *)ecs_get_mut_id(engine->world, target->eid, hp_comp);
            if (hp) { *hp = target->health; ecs_modified_id(engine->world, target->eid, hp_comp); }

            if (td_comp) {
                ecs_add_id(engine->world, target->eid, td_comp);
            }

            /* Record who this unit attacked (Weapon.attacked is second field, offset sizeof(int32_t)) */
            if (wpn_comp && ecs_has_id(engine->world, units[i].eid, wpn_comp)) {
                void *wpn = ecs_get_mut_id(engine->world, units[i].eid, wpn_comp);
                if (wpn) {
                    ecs_entity_t *attacked = (ecs_entity_t *)((char *)wpn + sizeof(int32_t));
                    *attacked = target->eid;
                    ecs_modified_id(engine->world, units[i].eid, wpn_comp);
                }
            }
        }
    }
}

/* ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ despawn ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ */

static void avk_despawn(Engine *engine) {
    if (is_simulation_paused(engine)) return;
    ecs_entity_t hp_comp = ecs_lookup(engine->world, "Health");
    if (!hp_comp) return;

    /* Collect entities to delete (can't delete during iteration) */
    ecs_entity_t to_delete[4096];
    int del_count = 0;

    ecs_query_t *q = ecs_query(engine->world, {
        .terms = {{ .id = hp_comp }, { .id = engine->user_entity_tag }},
        .cache_kind = EcsQueryCacheNone
    });
    ecs_iter_t it = ecs_query_iter(engine->world, q);
    while (ecs_query_next(&it)) {
        for (int i = 0; i < it.count; i++) {
            const int32_t *hp = (const int32_t *)ecs_get_id(engine->world, it.entities[i], hp_comp);
            if (hp && *hp <= 0 && del_count < 4096)
                to_delete[del_count++] = it.entities[i];
        }
    }
    ecs_query_fini(q);

    for (int i = 0; i < del_count; i++)
        ecs_delete(engine->world, to_delete[i]);
}

/* ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ spawn ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ */

static void avk_spawn(Engine *engine) {
    if (is_simulation_paused(engine)) return;
    ecs_entity_t sr_comp = ecs_lookup(engine->world, "SpawnRequest");
    ecs_entity_t loc_comp = ecs_lookup(engine->world, "Location");
    if (!sr_comp || !loc_comp) return;

    /* Collect spawn requests */
    typedef struct { ecs_entity_t eid; char template[64]; int x, y; } SpawnReq;
    SpawnReq reqs[4096];
    int req_count = 0;

    ecs_query_t *q = ecs_query(engine->world, {
        .terms = {{ .id = sr_comp }, { .id = loc_comp }},
        .cache_kind = EcsQueryCacheNone
    });
    ecs_iter_t it = ecs_query_iter(engine->world, q);
    while (ecs_query_next(&it)) {
        for (int i = 0; i < it.count && req_count < 4096; i++) {
            ecs_entity_t eid = it.entities[i];
            const void *sr = ecs_get_id(engine->world, eid, sr_comp);
            const void *loc = ecs_get_id(engine->world, eid, loc_comp);
            if (!sr || !loc) continue;

            const char *tmpl = *(const char *const *)sr;
            if (!tmpl) continue;

            reqs[req_count].eid = eid;
            snprintf(reqs[req_count].template, 64, "%s", tmpl);
            reqs[req_count].x = *(const int32_t *)loc;
            reqs[req_count].y = *((const int32_t *)loc + 1);
            req_count++;
        }
    }
    ecs_query_fini(q);

    /* Process */
    for (int i = 0; i < req_count; i++) {
        ecs_entity_t spawned = engine_entity_spawn(engine, reqs[i].template, NULL);
        if (spawned && loc_comp) {
            ecs_add_id(engine->world, spawned, loc_comp);
            int32_t *loc = (int32_t *)ecs_get_mut_id(engine->world, spawned, loc_comp);
            if (loc) {
                loc[0] = reqs[i].x; loc[1] = reqs[i].y;
                ecs_modified_id(engine->world, spawned, loc_comp);
            }
        }
        ecs_delete(engine->world, reqs[i].eid);
    }
}

/* ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ game_over ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ */

static void avk_app_stop(Engine *engine) {
    if (is_simulation_paused(engine)) return;
    ecs_entity_t red_comp = ecs_lookup(engine->world, "RedFaction");
    ecs_entity_t blue_comp = ecs_lookup(engine->world, "BlueFaction");
    ecs_entity_t hp_comp = ecs_lookup(engine->world, "Health");
    if (!red_comp || !blue_comp || !hp_comp) return;

    bool has_red = false, has_blue = false;

    /* Check for existing red units (not health ‚ÄĒ despawn handles dead units next turn) */
    ecs_query_t *qr = ecs_query(engine->world, {
        .terms = {{ .id = red_comp }, { .id = engine->user_entity_tag }},
        .cache_kind = EcsQueryCacheNone
    });
    ecs_iter_t itr = ecs_query_iter(engine->world, qr);
    while (ecs_query_next(&itr)) {
        if (itr.count > 0) { has_red = true; ecs_iter_fini(&itr); break; }
    }
    ecs_query_fini(qr);

    /* Check for existing blue units */
    ecs_query_t *qb = ecs_query(engine->world, {
        .terms = {{ .id = blue_comp }, { .id = engine->user_entity_tag }},
        .cache_kind = EcsQueryCacheNone
    });
    ecs_iter_t itb = ecs_query_iter(engine->world, qb);
    while (ecs_query_next(&itb)) {
        if (itb.count > 0) { has_blue = true; ecs_iter_fini(&itb); break; }
    }
    ecs_query_fini(qb);

    if (!has_red) {
        engine->game_over = true;
        snprintf(engine->game_over_message, sizeof(engine->game_over_message), "Knights Win");
    }
    if (!has_blue) {
        engine->game_over = true;
        snprintf(engine->game_over_message, sizeof(engine->game_over_message), "Archers Win");
    }
}

/* ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ Registration ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ */

void avk_register_native_systems(Engine *engine) {
    /* Ensure TookDamage component exists */
    ensure_took_damage_comp(engine);

    engine_system_register_native(engine, "start_of_turn", avk_start_of_turn);
    engine_system_register_native(engine, "app_start", avk_app_start);
    engine_system_register_native(engine, "movement", avk_movement);
    engine_system_register_native(engine, "attack", avk_attack);
    engine_system_register_native(engine, "despawn", avk_despawn);
    engine_system_register_native(engine, "spawn", avk_spawn);
    engine_system_register_native(engine, "app_stop", avk_app_stop);
}
#ifndef AVK_SYSTEMS_H
#define AVK_SYSTEMS_H

#include "engine/engine.h"

/* Register all native archer systems on an engine.
   Replaces Lua systems with C implementations for the same names. */
void avk_register_native_systems(Engine *engine);

#endif
#include "test.h"
#include "../src/engine/engine.h"
#include "../src/engine/simulation.h"
#include "../src/engine/app.h"
#include "../src/engine/history.h"
#include "../src/engine/components.h"

static Engine *engine;

static void count_factions(int *archers, int *knights) {
    *archers = 0; *knights = 0;
    ecs_entity_t hp_comp = ecs_lookup(engine->world, "Health");
    ecs_entity_t red_comp = ecs_lookup(engine->world, "RedFaction");
    ecs_entity_t blue_comp = ecs_lookup(engine->world, "BlueFaction");
    if (!hp_comp) return;
    EntityList list = engine_entity_list(engine);
    for (int i = 0; i < list.count; i++) {
        ecs_entity_t eid = list.items[i].id;
        const int32_t *hp = (const int32_t *)ecs_get_id(engine->world, eid, hp_comp);
        if (!hp || *hp <= 0) continue;
        if (red_comp && ecs_has_id(engine->world, eid, red_comp)) (*archers)++;
        else if (blue_comp && ecs_has_id(engine->world, eid, blue_comp)) (*knights)++;
    }
    engine_entity_list_free(&list);
}

static void setup_game(int map_size) {
    engine = engine_init(NULL);
    snprintf(engine->sandboxes_dir, sizeof(engine->sandboxes_dir), "./sandboxes/");
    engine_sandbox_select(engine, "avk");
    AppStartResult asr;
    engine_app_start(engine, NULL, &asr);
    ecs_entity_t map = engine_entity_create(engine, "Map");
    char vals[64];
    snprintf(vals, sizeof(vals), "x: %d, y: %d", map_size, map_size);
    engine_entity_add_component(engine, map, "MapSize", vals);
}

static void advance(int turns) {
    for (int i = 0; i < turns; i++) {
        TurnResult tr;
        if (!engine_sim_turn(engine, &tr)) break;
        engine_turn_result_free(&tr);
    }
}

static void unpause(void) {
    ecs_entity_t gs = ecs_lookup(engine->world, "GameState");
    ecs_entity_t sp = ecs_lookup(engine->world, "SimulationPaused");
    if (gs && sp) ecs_remove_id(engine->world, gs, sp);
}

/* ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ Rewind basics ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ */

TEST(rewind_restores_turn_counter) {
    setup_game(100);
    advance(10);
    ASSERT_EQ(engine->turn_counter, 10);

    engine_sim_rewind(engine, 5);
    ASSERT_EQ(engine->turn_counter, 5);
    ASSERT(is_simulation_paused(engine));

    engine_fini(engine);
}

TEST(rewind_clears_game_over) {
    setup_game(100);  /* Large enough to last several turns */
    advance(1000);
    ASSERT(engine->game_over);

    /* Rewind to a turn that exists in history (before game ended) */
    int oldest = history_oldest_turn(engine);
    ASSERT(oldest > 0);

    engine_sim_rewind(engine, oldest);
    ASSERT(!engine->game_over);
    ASSERT_EQ(engine->turn_counter, oldest);

    engine_fini(engine);
}

TEST(rewind_out_of_range_fails) {
    setup_game(100);
    advance(5);

    ASSERT(!engine_sim_rewind(engine, 0));   /* before history */
    ASSERT(!engine_sim_rewind(engine, 99));  /* after history */
    ASSERT_EQ(engine->turn_counter, 5);      /* unchanged */

    engine_fini(engine);
}

/* ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ Determinism: rewind to N, advance to M, verify counts match ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ */

TEST(determinism_rewind_and_replay) {
    setup_game(100);
    advance(10);

    int a_target, k_target;
    count_factions(&a_target, &k_target);
    int target_turn = engine->turn_counter;
    ASSERT(a_target > 0);  /* both factions still alive */
    ASSERT(k_target > 0);

    /* Rewind to 5, advance to 10 ‚ÄĒ should match */
    engine_sim_rewind(engine, 5);
    unpause();
    advance(5);

    int a, k;
    count_factions(&a, &k);
    ASSERT_EQ(engine->turn_counter, target_turn);
    ASSERT_EQ(a, a_target);
    ASSERT_EQ(k, k_target);

    engine_fini(engine);
}

TEST(determinism_repeated_rewind_cycles) {
    setup_game(100);
    advance(10);

    int a_target, k_target;
    count_factions(&a_target, &k_target);

    /* Rewind 5, advance 5, repeat 5 times ‚ÄĒ every iteration should match */
    for (int trial = 0; trial < 5; trial++) {
        engine_sim_rewind(engine, 5);
        unpause();
        advance(5);

        int a, k;
        count_factions(&a, &k);
        ASSERT_EQ(a, a_target);
        ASSERT_EQ(k, k_target);
    }

    engine_fini(engine);
}

TEST(determinism_rewind_to_start) {
    setup_game(100);
    advance(10);

    int a_target, k_target;
    count_factions(&a_target, &k_target);
    int target_turn = engine->turn_counter;

    /* Rewind to turn 1, replay all the way to target */
    engine_sim_rewind(engine, 1);
    unpause();
    advance(target_turn - 1);

    int a, k;
    count_factions(&a, &k);
    ASSERT_EQ(engine->turn_counter, target_turn);
    ASSERT_EQ(a, a_target);
    ASSERT_EQ(k, k_target);

    engine_fini(engine);
}

/* ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ Pause behavior ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ */

TEST(paused_turn_does_not_advance) {
    setup_game(100);
    advance(5);

    int a_before, k_before;
    count_factions(&a_before, &k_before);

    engine_sim_rewind(engine, 3);
    /* Still paused ‚ÄĒ run a turn, nothing should change */
    TurnResult tr;
    engine_sim_turn(engine, &tr);
    engine_turn_result_free(&tr);

    ASSERT_EQ(engine->turn_counter, 3);
    ASSERT(is_simulation_paused(engine));

    engine_fini(engine);
}

TEST(unpause_resumes_simulation) {
    setup_game(100);
    advance(5);

    engine_sim_rewind(engine, 3);
    ASSERT(is_simulation_paused(engine));

    unpause();
    ASSERT(!is_simulation_paused(engine));

    /* Advance should work now */
    TurnResult tr;
    engine_sim_turn(engine, &tr);
    engine_turn_result_free(&tr);
    ASSERT_EQ(engine->turn_counter, 4);

    engine_fini(engine);
}

/* ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ History query ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ */

TEST(history_tracks_turns) {
    setup_game(100);
    advance(10);

    ASSERT_EQ(history_newest_turn(engine), 10);
    ASSERT_EQ(history_oldest_turn(engine), 1);

    engine_fini(engine);
}

TEST(history_truncated_on_rewind) {
    setup_game(100);
    advance(10);
    ASSERT_EQ(history_newest_turn(engine), 10);

    engine_sim_rewind(engine, 5);
    ASSERT_EQ(history_newest_turn(engine), 5);

    engine_fini(engine);
}

int main(void) {
    TEST_SUITE("Rewind Basics");
    RUN(rewind_restores_turn_counter);
    RUN(rewind_clears_game_over);
    RUN(rewind_out_of_range_fails);

    TEST_SUITE("Rewind Determinism");
    RUN(determinism_rewind_and_replay);
    RUN(determinism_repeated_rewind_cycles);
    RUN(determinism_rewind_to_start);

    TEST_SUITE("Pause Behavior");
    RUN(paused_turn_does_not_advance);
    RUN(unpause_resumes_simulation);

    TEST_SUITE("History");
    RUN(history_tracks_turns);
    RUN(history_truncated_on_rewind);

    TEST_RESULTS();
}
